The paper deals with the problem of estimating nonlinear dynamic models from data, which is a topic in system identification (cs.SY). The paper also discusses the use of semidefinite programming (SDP) and regularization, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper proposes a new algorithm for solving the SDP problem, which is a topic in numerical analysis and optimization (cs.NE, cs.SI).
